I’m going back and forth on this one. I’m going to leave a tentative upvote here, but I might come back later and change it.

The worldbuilding here is its greatest strength. It reminds me of the plastic knife scp whose number I can’t remember, in that it feels quite fleshed out. The execution here is also tightened up from the draft I read, and it’s quite a more enjoyable read.

The execution is also my biggest reason I considered downvoting. It still jumps around quite a bit, which makes it feel jarring at points. The ending also leaves quite a bit to be desired; the ending lines don’t sting to me, and the dialogue is a bit purple for my tastes.

+1 for now.







